.SH NAME
WorkerGlobalScope.fonts \- WorkerGlobalScope: fonts property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]fonts\f[B]\f[R] property of the
\f[CR]WorkerGlobalScope\f[R] interface returns the
\f[CR]FontFaceSet\f[R] interface of the worker.
.PP
This property is part of the CSS Font Loading API.
.SH VALUE
The returned value is the \f[CR]FontFaceSet\f[R] interface of the
worker.
The \f[CR]FontFaceSet\f[R] interface is useful for loading new fonts,
checking the status of previously loaded fonts etc.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Doing operation after all fonts are loaded
.IP
.EX
fonts.ready.then(() \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  \f[I]// Any operation that needs to be done only after all the fonts\f[R]
  \f[I]// have finished loading can go here.\f[R]
});
.EE
